os laboratory, the Pentagon and State Department, the Congress, and the White House. But as they clearly show, once Truman made his decision in 1950, resistance to the H-bomb opportunistically shifted to new debates about the development of tactical nuclear weapons, continental air defense, and other aspects of nuclear weapons policy. What Super-Bomb reveals is that in many ways the H-bomb struggle was a proxy battle over the morality and effectiveness of strategic bombardment and the role and doctrine of the US Strategic Air Command.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aArms racexHistoryy20th century. 0aHydrogen bombxGovernment policyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aHydrogen bombzUnited StatesxHistory. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSecurity Studies. 4aU.S. History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh  aH-bomb, oral history, strategic bombardment, morality, decision-making.1 aSchilling, Warner R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501745171zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501745171423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501745171/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2